body:
I think to have found a bug on Tokeniser.read doing the parse of this url "http://www.tpwd.state.tx.us/exptexas/programs/".
I use the call Jsoup.parse(htmlCode, "UTF-8");

I have solved the problem with this little patch on line 1172 of TokeniserState.java (Jsoup 1.6.1 source):
There is a call to 
char c = r.current(); 
before the switch and there isn't any call to r.advance(); or to r.consume() internal at case nullChar.

Comment {
        void read(Tokeniser t, CharacterReader r) {
            char c = r.current();
            switch (c) {
                case '-':
                    t.advanceTransition(CommentEndDash);
                    break;
                case nullChar:
                    t.error(this);
                    t.commentPending.data.append(replacementChar);
                    // Patch to avoid a dangerous loop
                    // Jsoup 1.6.1 source, line 1172 of TokeniserState.java
                    // I have here a loop on the same null character because the CharacterRead r doesn't increase:
                    // Added r.consume to continue without loop that generate a loop with OutOfMemory java heap
                    r.consume();
                    break;
                case eof:
                    t.eofError(this);
                    t.emitCommentPending();
                    t.transition(Data);
                    break;
                default:
                    t.commentPending.data.append(r.consumeToAny('-', nullChar));
            }
        }
    },

Thanks for all
